      "question": "A solar energy startup is designing a rectangular field for solar panels. The length of the field is $3$ m more than twice its width. The area of the field is $90$ m$^2$. Let the width of the field be $x$ meters.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "Which of the following quadratic equations represents the given situation?",
          "answer": "(A)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $2x^2 + 3x - 90 = 0$",
            "(B) $2x^2 - 3x - 90 = 0$",
            "(C) $x^2 + 3x - 90 = 0$",
            "(D) $2x^2 + 3x + 90 = 0$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the width of the rectangular field.",
          "answer": "$6$ m",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Set up the equation $x(2x + 3) = 90$.",
              "Expand to get $2x^2 + 3x - 90 = 0$.",
              "Factorise the quadratic: $2x^2 + 15x - 12x - 90 = 0$.",
              "$x(2x + 15) - 6(2x + 15) = 0$.",
              "$(x - 6)(2x + 15) = 0$.",
              "Since width cannot be negative, $x = 6$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$2x^2 + 3x - 90 = 0 \\\\ 2x^2 + 15x - 12x - 90 = 0 \\\\ x(2x + 15) - 6(2x + 15) = 0 \\\\ (x - 6)(2x + 15) = 0 \\\\ x = 6, x = -7.5 \\\\ x = 6$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the length of the rectangular field?",
          "answer": "(C)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $12$ m",
            "(B) $14$ m",
            "(C) $15$ m",
            "(D) $18$ m"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Calculate the discriminant $D$ of the quadratic equation formed in part (i).",
          "answer": "$729$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Identify $a=2$, $b=3$, $c=-90$.",
              "Use $D = b^2 - 4ac$.",
              "$D = (3)^2 - 4(2)(-90)$.",
              "$D = 9 + 720 = 729$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$D = b^2 - 4ac \\\\ D = (3)^2 - 4(2)(-90) \\\\ D = 9 + 720 \\\\ D = 729$"
          }
        }
      ],
